Incident: Possible SQL injection detected

Indicators:
Alert Trigger Reason : Requested URL Contains OR 1 = 1 
Source IP: 61.177.172.87
Source port: 49821
Destination IP: 172.16.17.16
Destination Port: 443

Investigation:
Understanding why alert was triggered:
  Request Body Contains whoami string

Traffic information:
SOURCE:
  After researching ip address using ARIN Whois/RDAP, The IP address is owned by CHINANET jiangsu province network

DESTINATION:
  The destination is a webserver on the simulated SIEM.

PROTOCOL
  The protocol being used: HTTPS

Findings:
  An attacker using a telecom services domain exectuted remote commands on a company web server by putting commands in POST request paramaters

This user is not on the company network.

After looking through logs the attacker did multiple requests executing commands on the webservers terminal. This traffic is malicous.

Just to be sure, I analyzed the email logs to check if this was a scheduled test, it was not. Nothing like that was ever mentioned.

The traffic flow is Internet -> Company network.

After analysic the logs, the injection attempts all resulted in response code 200, so I looked at our endpoints to see the processes on the web server, and the commands did go through on the webserver.

Conclusion:
True positive alert.

Response:
Commands when through, first contain the system, then escalate the alert.
